cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG

The paper discusses the process of generating a set of conditions that could serve as a specification for a logic program, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also proposes a definition of program completion for a large class of programs in the input language of the ASP grounder GRINGO, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper's focus on examining the output produced by software to help programmers see more clearly what their program does and to what degree its behavior conforms with their expectations suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper's consideration for publication in Theory and Practice of Logic Programming indicates a possible connection to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
